334
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:07,790
-I am.
-I'm not.

335
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:09,090
Right, ready? Watch this.

336
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,200
RICHARD:
He's going in. First bite.

337
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,970
Oh, it's a big fall
of chocolate!

338
00:17:13,030 --> 00:17:15,230
JEREMY: Mm.
-It's a heavy sprinkling,
that.

339
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,300
That is just a light dusting
of chocolate.

340
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:19,200
-A light dusting, yeah, OK.
-Right, James May.

341
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:23,920
Moving over to James May
and his Double Decker.
This is exciting, isn't it?

342
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:27,420
-This is a great
car programme.
-Groundbreaking stuff, yeah.

343
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,680
-Quiet, please.
-I can't believe...

344
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:33,120
-I can't believe this hasn't
been done before.
-(LAUGHTER)

345
00:17:33,220 --> 00:17:35,220
He's going in.
He's taking a bite.

346
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:39,100
His poor old gnash...
His teeth!

347
00:17:39,230 --> 00:17:40,500
-Oh!
-(AUDIENCE GASPS)

348
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:44,390
It's a catastrophic fall!
The clear winner...

349
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:48,860
The Double Decker
is worse than the Flake.

350
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:51,910
There's the Flake.
There's the Double Decker.

351
00:17:51,970 --> 00:17:54,640
So, there we are.
Using science,
we have now established...

352
00:17:54,710 --> 00:17:58,080
...if you've got a Volvo,
don't have a Double Decker.

353
00:17:58,140 --> 00:17:59,410
-Ever.
-(LAUGHTER)

354
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:01,950
Or an ice cream, because
he... Oh, no, forget it.

355
00:18:02,010 --> 00:18:06,050
Let's move a little further
along Conversation Street,
shall we?

356
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:07,930
Erm...
A few weeks ago, Amazon,

357
00:18:07,990 --> 00:18:11,260
they ran an advert
for our show, and we're
rather pleased with it.

358
00:18:11,290 --> 00:18:12,520
See, it's got everything in.

359
00:18:12,590 --> 00:18:14,720
-Yeah, the sense of travel.
-Logo.

360
00:18:14,790 --> 00:18:17,160
-And there's even the goat.
-Yeah, no, that's perfect.

361
00:18:17,260 --> 00:18:21,100
-Everything you need there.
-All you need for the advert.
It's on the screen.

362
00:18:21,170 --> 00:18:22,740
-It's good, isn't it?
-(LAUGHTER)

363
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:27,170
Yeah. All the essentials are
there. Everything you need.

364
00:18:27,270 --> 00:18:28,640
Everything you need to see.

365
00:18:30,780 --> 00:18:32,880
-(RICHARD LAUGHS)
JEREMY: Actually...

