00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:34,090
All the important stuff.

367
00:18:34,150 --> 00:18:35,750
Hammond,
I'm sorry to do this,

368
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:38,760
but before the show launched,
Amazon did another advert,
OK,

369
00:18:38,820 --> 00:18:41,760
which somebody sent to me
on a tweet,
which I screen grabbed,

370
00:18:41,820 --> 00:18:44,690
so the quality's not good,
but I have brought it along.

371
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:45,930
Here it is.

372
00:18:45,990 --> 00:18:47,020
Oh, for God's sake!

373
00:18:47,090 --> 00:18:48,490
(LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE)

374
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:52,660
(GROANS)

375
00:18:52,730 --> 00:18:56,530
I like their marketing
department a lot.

376
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,370
I think that's enough
Conversation Street,

377
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,980
so let's get back
to our film.

378
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:03,380
Yes. Earlier on,
I was in the right-hand-drive
Ford Mustang,

379
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,440
showing it the sights
around our country.

380
00:19:05,510 --> 00:19:07,310
Unfortunately, he turned up

381
00:19:07,310 --> 00:19:11,510
and tried to argue that
the similarly priced
Ford Focus was a better bet.

382
00:19:11,580 --> 00:19:17,320
-Yeah, I did do that.
-I responded by driving off
and refusing to talk to you.

383
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:18,700
A bit rudely, I thought.

384
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:27,930
I'm sorry, this is my film,
my tour of England,

385
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,530
and I didn't want him
spoiling it.

386
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:36,340
This thing's bloody awesome.

387
00:19:38,910 --> 00:19:39,910
Listen to that bellow.

388
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:42,120
This thing squats
on its haunches.

389
00:19:42,180 --> 00:19:44,750
This is what
it's built to do.

390
00:19:44,820 --> 00:19:50,800
Every crackle, pop and bang
is just connected to every
synapse and sinew in me.

391
00:19:53,790 --> 00:19:55,360
Oh, no.

392
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:03,810
This is like a first date
for me, and on a first date,

393
00:20:03,870 --> 00:20:07,700
you don't want a fat,
balding uncle tagging along.

394
00:20:09,380 --> 00:20:12,320
So what I'm gonna do now...
is lose him.

395
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:19,320
It's Hammer Time!
Shock and awe!

396
00:20:26,690 --> 00:20:28,760
It's Bond versus Bourne.

397
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,840
(HORNS BLARING)

398
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:40,410
He's got five litres.
I've only got 2.3.

399
00:20:40,470 --> 00:20:43,510
Is he going twice as fast?
No, he is not.

400
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:51,760
Corner coming up.
There's no need to panic
any more in a Mustang,

401
00:20:51,820 --> 00:20:53,690
because, for the first time,

402
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:56,080
the Mustang has
independent rear suspension.

403
00:21:02,260 --> 00:21:03,590
Ooh! (LAUGHS)

404
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:09,810
The cornering speeds
this thing can achieve...
beggar belief.

405
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,450
(CHUCKLES)

406
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:22,810
How does it grip that well?!

407
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:30,360
(LAUGHS) I'm in a car chase
in a Mustang.

408
00:21:30,460 --> 00:21:31,830
I am Steve McQueen.

409
00:21:37,860 --> 00:21:39,560
Try that on.

410
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,580
I've got it in Sport Mode,

411
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,980
which makes the exhaust
pop and bang.

412
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,050
(POPPING)

413
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:51,120
Woohoo! Mine! (LAUGHS)

414
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,780
RICHARD: Oh, my God!

415
00:21:59,150 --> 00:22:01,020
Flat out, yeah.

416
00:22:03,190 --> 00:22:05,300
And it still grips!

417
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:08,800
What is the point of traction
control on this thing?

418
00:22:08,860 --> 00:22:11,960
It's like putting a
nymphomania control on a nun.

419
00:22:22,810 --> 00:22:24,820
Oh, God!

420
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,210
(HORN BLARES)

421
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:40,830
Where's he gone?

422
00:22:42,430 --> 00:22:45,540
How did he do that?
How did he get away from me

423
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:48,370
in something
from the 18th century?

424
00:22:48,430 --> 00:22:50,000
Especially when I'm driving

425
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:54,410
what is basically
a turbocharged barnacle.

426
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:59,570
This has the most
sophisticated
four-wheel-drive system

427
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:01,120
fitted to any car.

428
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,710
Not even a Nissan GTR
could live with this.

429
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:14,070
The Mustang, well,
that's for cruising down

430
00:23:14,130 --> 00:23:18,140
the Pacific Coast Highway,
listening to Don Henley.

431
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:21,140
This is for storming up
the Stelvio Pass,

432
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,830
listening to the Clash.

433
00:23:26,210 --> 00:23:30,010
But while it's a grippy,
technological masterpiece,

434
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:35,490
it still has the blue-collar
character of its ancestors.

435
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:40,820
In many ways, this reminds me
of the old Escort Cosworth,
and that was a great car.

436
00:23:40,890 --> 00:23:43,630
I actually had one in
the '90s. I called it Gary.

437
00:23:43,690 --> 00:23:48,090
It started every morning
and it always went,
"Do you want some?!"

438
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:50,660
It was just
John Terry, really,
with windscreen wipers.

439
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:56,800
RICHARD: Meanwhile,
having got rid of the ape,

440
00:23:56,870 --> 00:23:59,840
I was back on
my sightseeing tour.

441
00:23:59,910 --> 00:24:02,650
This is our Cheddar Gorge.

442
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:06,710
Obviously it's not as big
as your gorge.

443
00:24:06,780 --> 00:24:08,620
The Grand Canyon is bigger.

444
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:11,950
Well, it's longer
and deeper... and wider.

445
00:24:12,020 --> 00:24:14,660
Mm. But it doesn't have
any cheese in it.

446
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:16,380
Why can't you
just leave me alone?

447
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:19,360
I'm just saying, everything
in America comes with cheese,

448
00:24:19,430 --> 00:24:21,030
apart from the Grand Canyon.

449
00:24:21,090 --> 00:24:24,790
Whereas this canyon
does come with cheese,
and it's delicious.

