REPORTER: And so to the first
Le Mans practice session.

957
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:31,370
JAMES: On its first outing,
the renamed GT40 was fast,

958
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:34,180
but it was also
terrifyingly unstable,

959
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:37,250
spinning its wheels
on the straights.

960
00:49:37,310 --> 00:49:39,320
I'm not talking about
when you set off,

961
00:49:39,380 --> 00:49:42,750
I mean it was happening
at 170mph!

962
00:49:45,550 --> 00:49:48,850
Now, the problem was either
aerodynamics or suspension,

963
00:49:48,920 --> 00:49:50,260
but they never found out,

964
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:55,660
because, later that day,
the car crashed at 160mph.

965
00:49:55,730 --> 00:49:58,500
Well, that was OK. They had
a spare one, of course.

966
00:49:58,560 --> 00:50:01,060
The next day,
that crashed as well.

967
00:50:01,170 --> 00:50:03,840
Le Mans
was just two months away.

968
00:50:06,770 --> 00:50:13,610
Against all odds,
Ford got their act together
in time for the 1964 race.

969
00:50:13,680 --> 00:50:15,750
REPORTER: The Le Mans
24 Hour Race at last,

970
00:50:15,810 --> 00:50:19,410
and three gleaming Ford GTs
are present.

971
00:50:19,480 --> 00:50:21,510
JAMES:
But during the race itself,

972
00:50:21,590 --> 00:50:25,060
all the cars broke down
or caught fire,

973
00:50:25,120 --> 00:50:27,120
leaving bitter rivals Ferrari

974
00:50:27,190 --> 00:50:31,160
to take another
one-two-three victory.

975
00:50:34,330 --> 00:50:38,160
In Detroit, Henry Ford
decreed that they would be
back next year

976
00:50:38,240 --> 00:50:40,380
to take on Ferrari again.

977
00:50:40,440 --> 00:50:42,280
And to head up the campaign,

978
00:50:42,340 --> 00:50:45,670
he turned to
an American motorsport hero.

979
00:50:45,740 --> 00:50:48,970
My name's Carroll Shelby and
performance is my business.

980
00:50:49,050 --> 00:50:52,150
Shelby was a former
chicken farmer from Texas

981
00:50:52,220 --> 00:50:55,660
who took nitroglycerin pills
to keep his heart going.

982
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:58,080
But he'd also racked up
countless victories

983
00:50:58,160 --> 00:51:00,630
as a driver and team owner.

984
00:51:00,690 --> 00:51:03,590
Given the task of turning
the GT40 into a winner,

985
00:51:03,660 --> 00:51:05,960
he put his top man
on the job.

986
00:51:06,030 --> 00:51:07,530
Coming up is Ken Miles,

987
00:51:07,600 --> 00:51:11,240
one of the best
sport-car drivers in America.

988
00:51:11,240 --> 00:51:15,710
Miles was a former
Second World War tank
commander from Birmingham -

989
00:51:15,770 --> 00:51:18,600
the one in England,
not Alabama.

990
00:51:18,680 --> 00:51:20,580
He was renowned
for speaking his mind

991
00:51:20,650 --> 00:51:23,750
and developing racing cars.

992
00:51:23,810 --> 00:51:25,510
Miles took the car
for a shakedown.

993
00:51:25,580 --> 00:51:28,810
Then he got out
and he told Shelby
and the Ford executives,

994
00:51:28,890 --> 00:51:30,490
"It's bloody awful!"

995
00:51:30,560 --> 00:51:32,260
Then he got to work,

996
00:51:32,290 --> 00:51:34,750
improving the brakes,
the engine,

997
00:51:34,830 --> 00:51:36,800
the aerodynamics,
the handling,

998
00:51:36,860 --> 00:51:41,860
and taming
the car's terrifying
high-speed instability.

999
00:51:41,930 --> 00:51:44,960
However, and even though he
and his team took amphetamine

1000
00:51:45,040 --> 00:51:46,840
so that they could
stay awake all night,

1001
00:51:46,900 --> 00:51:51,870
there simply wasn't time
to develop the car properly
for Le Mans.

1002
00:51:51,940 --> 00:51:54,270
The GT40
may have been faster,

1003
00:51:54,350 --> 00:51:56,420
but it was still fragile.

1004
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:58,280
At the 1965 race,

1005
00:51:58,350 --> 00:52:00,860
six cars started,
none finished,

1006
00:52:00,920 --> 00:52:04,830
and the Italians
humiliated Ford once again.

1007
00:52:06,890 --> 00:52:09,820
So, untold millions
of dollars had been spent

1008
00:52:09,890 --> 00:52:13,430
since the first GT40 emerged
from this building here,

1009
00:52:13,500 --> 00:52:17,610
and yet not one car
had even finished the race.

1010
00:52:17,670 --> 00:52:19,380
So Ford now faced
a difficult choice -

1011
00:52:19,440 --> 00:52:23,480
he could throw in the towel
against Ferrari,
or he could fight on.

1012
00:52:23,540 --> 00:52:26,710
What he actually did was
he had some business cards
printed,

1013
00:52:26,780 --> 00:52:29,320
and he distributed them
to his Le Mans team.

1014
00:52:29,350 --> 00:52:32,460
And on the cards it said,
"You'd better win."

1015
00:52:32,520 --> 00:52:34,090
And so, a year later,

1016
00:52:34,150 --> 00:52:36,780
the American giant
returned to Le Mans

1017
00:52:36,850 --> 00:52:40,890
with its hopes
resting on this.

1018
00:52:40,960 --> 00:52:42,330
(ENGINE REVVING)

1019
00:52:48,430 --> 00:52:49,900
OK, viewers,

1020
00:52:49,970 --> 00:52:54,980
this is historic-race-car
bucket-list moment
number two,

1021
00:52:55,040 --> 00:52:57,780
because this is
an actual GT40

1022
00:52:57,840 --> 00:53:01,570
that competed at Le Mans
in 1966.

1023
00:53:03,980 --> 00:53:07,350
All right, don't go mad, May,
it's worth 15-million quid.

1024
00:53:08,750 --> 00:53:11,350
Sod it!
Let's make some noise!

1025
00:53:17,830 --> 00:53:18,770
Oh, yes!

1026
00:53:21,470 --> 00:53:23,070
In this new GT40,

1027
00:53:23,130 --> 00:53:27,030
Ken Miles had racked up
thousands of test hours.

1028
00:53:27,100 --> 00:53:30,570
Now the car was no longer
horribly unstable,

1029
00:53:30,640 --> 00:53:34,970
but would sit rocksteady
at 210mph.

1030
00:53:35,050 --> 00:53:39,990
And the Brummie tank
commander had the backing of
Ford's huge R&D department,

1031
00:53:40,050 --> 00:53:42,750
who tackled the car's
appalling reliability.

1032
00:53:44,990 --> 00:53:47,660
The brakes no longer went
into thermal shock

1033
00:53:47,730 --> 00:53:50,070
at the end of
the long straight.

1034
00:53:50,130 --> 00:53:54,000
The engine and transmission
were run on
a computerised test rig

1035
00:53:54,060 --> 00:53:58,130
that simulated the whole of
the 24-Hour Le Mans race.

1036
00:53:58,200 --> 00:54:00,770
Now, that's standard practice
in Formula One today,

1037
00:54:00,840 --> 00:54:04,510
but in 1966
that was witchcraft.

1038
00:54:06,510 --> 00:54:09,440
They weren't mucking about,
these blokes.

1039
00:54:09,510 --> 00:54:12,140
But neither were
the opposition.

1040
00:54:12,220 --> 00:54:15,430
Over in Italy, in response
to the new threat,

1041
00:54:15,490 --> 00:54:17,860
Ferrari produced this.

1042
00:54:24,330 --> 00:54:29,000
Called the P3,
it looked as sleek as a GT40.

1043
00:54:29,070 --> 00:54:33,880
And at just 37.4 inches tall,
it was even lower.

1044
00:54:38,540 --> 00:54:40,470
Avanti!

1045
00:54:43,450 --> 00:54:45,760
Whoo! Holy mother!

1046
00:54:45,820 --> 00:54:49,160
I best be a little bit
careful on this narrow road.

1047
00:54:49,220 --> 00:54:51,960
It's worth £20 million.

1048
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:59,460
Where the GT40 boasted
a top speed of over 210mph,

1049
00:54:59,500 --> 00:55:02,710
the P3 maxed out at just 190.

1050
00:55:02,770 --> 00:55:08,880
But Enzo Ferrari was willing
to trade outright speed
for gains elsewhere.

1051
00:55:10,140 --> 00:55:12,610
The Ferrari was lighter,
it was more agile.

1052
00:55:12,680 --> 00:55:16,050
Ferrari reckoned
he could make up
the difference in the bends,

1053
00:55:16,110 --> 00:55:19,480
and he wouldn't have to stop
so often for fuel.

1054
00:55:21,090 --> 00:55:24,590
A David and Goliath battle
was looming.

1055
00:55:24,660 --> 00:55:30,200
At the 1966 Le Mans race,
Ford arrived with an armada -

1056
00:55:30,260 --> 00:55:33,490
eight cars,
20 tonnes of spares,

1057
00:55:33,560 --> 00:55:35,900
and a squad
of world-class drivers,

1058
00:55:35,970 --> 00:55:38,540
including Ken Miles himself.

1059
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:43,000
In comparison, Ferrari turned
up with just a trio of P3s,

1060
00:55:43,070 --> 00:55:44,970
but Enzo had an ace
up his sleeve -

1061
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:48,710
the undisputed
fastest driver on the planet,

1062
00:55:48,780 --> 00:55:53,290
Formula One World Champion
John Surtees.

1063
00:55:53,350 --> 00:55:59,690
He came to me and said,
"John... we've got to beat
the Fords. Go out and do it."

1064
00:55:59,760 --> 00:56:01,330
I thought
there was only one tactic -

1065
00:56:01,390 --> 00:56:05,020
to have at least one car
be the hare.

1066
00:56:05,100 --> 00:56:09,540
I said, "Look,
I don't mind being the hare."

1067
00:56:09,530 --> 00:56:11,330
"The moment
that flag goes down,

1068
00:56:11,400 --> 00:56:13,330
we need to be - bang - off,"

1069
00:56:13,400 --> 00:56:18,200
tempting the Ford drivers
to perhaps overdrive
a little bit.

1070
00:56:18,280 --> 00:56:21,220
If one could push them
hard enough for long enough,

1071
00:56:21,280 --> 00:56:26,420
then there is more
likelihood, obviously,
of being able to break them.

1072
00:56:26,550 --> 00:56:28,250
The plan was set.

1073
00:56:28,320 --> 00:56:32,560
But, as zero hour approached,
everything unravelled.

1074
00:56:32,620 --> 00:56:35,790
REPORTER: Shortly before
the race, we learned that
he wasn't going to drive,

1075
00:56:35,860 --> 00:56:37,590
and we asked him about it.

1076
00:56:37,660 --> 00:56:41,360
Yes, unfortunately
you've heard correct.
I won't be driving.

1077
00:56:41,430 --> 00:56:43,430
REPORTER: What is the reason?

1078
00:56:43,570 --> 00:56:46,580
Well, I suppose it's best
summed up at this stage

1079
00:56:46,600 --> 00:56:49,100
by saying
"political reasons."

1080
00:56:49,170 --> 00:56:51,440
JAMES: The problem was that
the Ferrari team manager

1081
00:56:51,580 --> 00:56:53,850
was playing
his own political game.

1082
00:56:53,910 --> 00:56:56,310
He had no particular liking
for Surtees,

1083
00:56:56,380 --> 00:56:57,940
and he nominated
another driver

1084
00:56:58,020 --> 00:57:01,060
to go out and start the race,
to be the hare,

1085
00:57:01,120 --> 00:57:06,700
even though Surtees
was clearly
the fastest man available.

1086
00:57:06,760 --> 00:57:11,300
SURTEES: And I just stormed
away, drove back, and
had it out with the old man.

1087
00:57:11,360 --> 00:57:13,590
As the Italian papers put it,

1088
00:57:13,630 --> 00:57:17,700
they showed a picture
of me walking out the gates
and saying,

1089
00:57:17,770 --> 00:57:22,610
"The divorce of John Surtees
and Enzo."

1090
00:57:24,780 --> 00:57:26,880
With Surtees out of the way,

1091
00:57:26,940 --> 00:57:30,110
the Fords took the top four
slots in qualifying.

1092
00:57:30,180 --> 00:57:34,610
And as the clock ticked down,
Henry Ford II
prepared to drop the flag,

1093
00:57:34,690 --> 00:57:40,530
praying that, this time,
he would get his revenge.

1094
00:57:40,630 --> 00:57:44,300
REPORTER:
Live from Le Mans, France,
it's the 24 Hours of Le Mans.

1095
00:57:46,030 --> 00:57:47,160
(CROWD CHEERING)

1096
00:57:57,110 --> 00:57:59,650
At first, the Fords
stormed into the lead.

1097
00:57:59,680 --> 00:58:01,520
But a few hours in,

1098
00:58:01,650 --> 00:58:07,660
it was beginning to look like
a depressing repeat
of '64 and '65.

1099
00:58:07,650 --> 00:58:10,480
As night fell, the Ferraris,
using their greater agility

1100
00:58:10,550 --> 00:58:12,450
and their greater
fuel efficiency,

1101
00:58:12,520 --> 00:58:14,550
were leading the race
one-two.

1102
00:58:14,660 --> 00:58:20,670
Four of the eight GT40s were
out of the race altogether.

1103
00:58:20,700 --> 00:58:25,710
Worse still, the Ford drivers
had strict orders
not to go balls-out

1104
00:58:25,770 --> 00:58:29,170
for fear
of breaking the cars.

1105
00:58:29,240 --> 00:58:32,310
But one man wasn't listening
to those orders.

1106
00:58:32,380 --> 00:58:34,250
Ken Miles
put the hammer down,

1107
00:58:34,310 --> 00:58:37,910
set blistering lap times,
and retook the lead for Ford.

1108
00:58:39,450 --> 00:58:42,690
The Ferraris had no response
to this crushing pace,

1109
00:58:42,690 --> 00:58:46,900
and by morning,
they had either
broken down or crashed.

1110
00:58:48,730 --> 00:58:51,800
That afternoon, Henry Ford
watched his cars cruise home

1111
00:58:51,860 --> 00:58:55,190
to a spectacular
one-two-three finish.

1112
00:58:58,300 --> 00:59:02,370
REPORTER: First place
for the Ford GT Mk II,

1113
00:59:02,440 --> 00:59:06,550
and a first-time win
for America at Le Mans.

1114
00:59:06,610 --> 00:59:10,710
JAMES: Ford would go on
to win their next four
Le Mans races.

1115
00:59:10,720 --> 00:59:13,890
But the man
who had contributed
so much to the team

1116
00:59:13,950 --> 00:59:16,020
didn't get to see
these triumphs.

1117
00:59:16,090 --> 00:59:19,730
Ken Miles was killed two
months after their first win,

1118
00:59:19,760 --> 00:59:22,430
testing the latest GT40.

1119
00:59:24,730 --> 00:59:28,340
It's impossible to calculate
how much Henry Ford spent

1120
00:59:28,400 --> 00:59:31,010
on his three-year campaign
to break Ferrari,

1121
00:59:31,070 --> 00:59:33,310
but experts reckon that,
at the very least,

1122
00:59:33,370 --> 00:59:38,800
in today's money,
it was £360 million.

1123
00:59:38,880 --> 00:59:42,750
Now, that's a big bill
for settling a spat
with an angry Italian.

1124
00:59:44,750 --> 00:59:47,290
But look what
we got out of it -

1125
00:59:47,350 --> 00:59:49,980
one of the world's
greatest cars.

1126
00:59:55,760 --> 00:59:56,960
(CHEERING)

1127
00:59:57,030 --> 00:59:58,500
RICHARD: Very good.

1128
00:59:58,560 --> 01:00:00,460
That was good. Very good.

1129
01:00:07,140 --> 01:00:09,240
-I hate you.
-I know.

1130
01:00:09,310 --> 01:00:14,250
No, but I really hate you
now, cos you've driven a
Ford GT40, and I never have.

1131
01:00:14,310 --> 01:00:16,940
I mean, next week
are you gonna lick
Helena Christensen?

1132
01:00:17,010 --> 01:00:18,480
-(LAUGHTER)
-Look...

1133
01:00:18,550 --> 01:00:21,920
I'm sure you could drive a
GT40 if you really wanted to.

1134
01:00:21,990 --> 01:00:23,490
I can't, I'm too tall.

1135
01:00:23,550 --> 01:00:25,380
Yeah, you mean fat.

1136
01:00:25,460 --> 01:00:26,860
(LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE)

1137
01:00:34,900 --> 01:00:37,310
-Tall.
-(LAUGHTER)

1138
01:00:37,370 --> 01:00:39,140
Horizontally tall.

1139
01:00:39,200 --> 01:00:40,270
(LAUGHTER)

1140
01:00:40,340 --> 01:00:42,540
Well, listen, whatever
dimension is the problem,

1141
01:00:42,610 --> 01:00:44,150
I can't drive one.

1142
01:00:44,210 --> 01:00:47,150
And on that terrible
disappointment,
it is time to end.

1143
01:00:47,210 --> 01:00:49,710
Thank you so much
for watching. Good night.

1144
01:00:49,780 --> 01:00:51,510
(CHEERING)

